**DAY 4 IMPLEMENTATION GUIDE**

Qdrant RAG Integration for n8n

Hybrid Approach: Static Core + Dynamic Knowledge Base

  ------------------------------- ---------------------------------------
  **Date:**                       February 2026

  **Plan Day:**                   Day 4 of 21

  **Classification:**             Internal Operations
  ------------------------------- ---------------------------------------

**What You\'ll Build Today**

Today you\'re upgrading your ELECTRON-2 workflow from a single giant
system prompt to a smart, modular system that pulls knowledge from your
Qdrant database automatically.

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **WHY THIS MATTERS**                                                  |
|                                                                       |
| Right now, if you want to ban a new phrase or change a brand color,   |
| you have to edit the entire 3,300-word system prompt. After today,    |
| you\'ll just add a new entry in Qdrant and the system picks it up     |
| automatically. Zero prompt editing needed.                            |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

**Before vs After**

  ----------------------------------- -----------------------------------
  **BEFORE (Day 3)**                  **AFTER (Day 4)**

  Everything hardcoded in one massive Split into static core (1,200
  system prompt (3,300 words)         words) + dynamic Qdrant knowledge

  Change a banned phrase = edit       Change a banned phrase = add entry
  system prompt manually              to Qdrant (auto-detected)

  \~1,800 input tokens every time     \~1,000-1,400 input tokens
  (expensive)                         (cheaper, pulls only what\'s
                                      needed)

  Same rules for every content type   Smart retrieval: Meals content gets
                                      Meals rules, TikTok gets TikTok
                                      tone
  ----------------------------------- -----------------------------------

**The Hybrid Approach Explained**

Think of ELECTRON-2 as having two parts of its brain:

**Part 1: Static Core (hardcoded in n8n)**

This never changes. It tells ELECTRON-2 WHO it is and HOW to work:

-   Agent identity (\"You are ELECTRON-2, the Content Architect for
    CorpFit\")

-   Output format (emoji headers, sections, self-check report)

-   Workflow steps (Parse \> Plan \> Create \> Check \> Output)

-   Safe framing rules (\"may support\" instead of \"cures\")

**Part 2: Dynamic Knowledge (pulled from Qdrant)**

This changes and grows over time. It tells ELECTRON-2 WHAT to follow:

-   Brand colors, fonts, visual guidelines

-   Platform-specific tone (TikTok casual, LinkedIn professional)

-   Module definitions (Steps, Workouts, Meals, Check-in, Events)

-   Banned phrases (the 55 words/phrases AI must never use)

-   Health safety rules and disclaimer templates

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **ANALOGY**                                                           |
|                                                                       |
| The static core is like a chef\'s training and cooking technique      |
| (doesn\'t change). The dynamic knowledge is like today\'s menu and    |
| ingredient restrictions (changes regularly). You don\'t retrain the   |
| chef every time you add a new dish --- you just update the menu.      |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

**Your Updated n8n Workflow**

Here\'s the complete workflow you\'ll build today, node by node:

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| WORKFLOW: ELECTRON-2 Content Generator v2 (RAG-Enhanced)              |
|                                                                       |
| \[Manual Trigger\]                                                    |
|                                                                       |
| \|                                                                    |
|                                                                       |
| v                                                                     |
|                                                                       |
| \[Set Node: Parse Brief\] \<\-- Extracts module, platform, funnel     |
| from your input                                                       |
|                                                                       |
| \|                                                                    |
|                                                                       |
| v                                                                     |
|                                                                       |
| \[Qdrant: Brand Rules\] \<\-- Searches Qdrant for relevant brand      |
| rules                                                                 |
|                                                                       |
| \|                                                                    |
|                                                                       |
| v                                                                     |
|                                                                       |
| \[Qdrant: Banned Phrases\] \<\-- Pulls banned phrases list from       |
| Qdrant                                                                |
|                                                                       |
| \|                                                                    |
|                                                                       |
| v                                                                     |
|                                                                       |
| \[Code Node: Assemble\] \<\-- Combines static prompt + Qdrant results |
|                                                                       |
| \|                                                                    |
|                                                                       |
| v                                                                     |
|                                                                       |
| \[HTTP Request: Claude\] \<\-- Sends assembled prompt to Claude API   |
|                                                                       |
| \|                                                                    |
|                                                                       |
| v                                                                     |
|                                                                       |
| \[Code Node: Parse Output\] \<\-- Extracts structured content from    |
| response                                                              |
|                                                                       |
| \|                                                                    |
|                                                                       |
| v                                                                     |
|                                                                       |
| \[Set Node: Store Result\] \<\-- Saves to PostgreSQL (future step)    |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

Total nodes: 7 (up from 2 in your Day 3 workflow). Each node does one
clear job.

**Step-by-Step Implementation**

Follow these steps in order. Each step tells you exactly what to click
and type in n8n.

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **BEFORE YOU START**                                                  |
|                                                                       |
| Make sure all your Docker services are running. Open Portainer at     |
| localhost:9000 and verify n8n, Qdrant, Ollama, and PostgreSQL         |
| containers are all green/running. Then open n8n at localhost:5678.    |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

**STEP 1: Open Your Existing Workflow**

In n8n, find and open the \"ELECTRON-2 Content Generator\" workflow you
built on Day 3. We\'ll modify this workflow rather than starting from
scratch.

1.  Go to localhost:5678

2.  Click on \"ELECTRON-2 Content Generator\" in your workflow list

3.  You should see: Manual Trigger \> HTTP Request (Claude API)

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **TIP**                                                               |
|                                                                       |
| Before making changes, click the three dots menu in the top-right and |
| select \"Duplicate\" to make a backup copy. Name it \"ELECTRON-2      |
| Content Generator v1 (backup)\". This way you can always go back if   |
| something breaks.                                                     |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

**STEP 2: Add the Set Node (Parse Brief)**

This node takes your production brief and extracts the key fields that
Qdrant will use to search for relevant rules.

**What to do:**

4.  Click the + button between Manual Trigger and HTTP Request

5.  Search for \"Set\" and add a Set node

6.  Rename it to \"Parse Brief\" (double-click the name)

7.  Click \"Add Value\" and add these fields:

  ----------------- ----------------- -----------------------------------
  **Field Name**    **Type**          **Value**

  **module**        String            meals (change per test)

  **platform**      String            tiktok (change per test)

  **funnel**        String            b2c (or b2b)

  **topic**         String            Desk stretches for office workers
                                      (your content topic)

  **duration**      String            30 seconds (target video length)
  ----------------- ----------------- -----------------------------------

*These values will flow through the rest of the workflow. In production,
these will come from QUANTUM\'s task tickets automatically.*

**STEP 3: Configure Qdrant Credentials in n8n**

Before adding Qdrant nodes, you need to tell n8n how to connect to your
Qdrant database.

**What to do:**

8.  In n8n, go to Settings (gear icon) \> Credentials

9.  Click \"Add Credential\"

10. Search for \"Qdrant\" and select it

11. Fill in these fields:

  ----------------------- -----------------------------------------------
  **Field**               **Value**

  **Qdrant URL**          http://qdrant:6333

  **API Key**             (leave empty --- your local Qdrant has no auth)
  ----------------------- -----------------------------------------------

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **IMPORTANT: Use \"qdrant\" not \"localhost\"**                       |
|                                                                       |
| Inside Docker, services talk to each other using their container      |
| names, not localhost. Your Qdrant container is named \"qdrant\", so   |
| n8n connects to http://qdrant:6333. You use localhost:6333 only when  |
| accessing Qdrant from your browser.                                   |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

12. Click \"Save\" --- name it \"CorpFit Qdrant\"

13. Click \"Test\" to verify the connection works (should show green
    checkmark)

**STEP 4: Add Qdrant Node: Brand Rules Search**

This node searches your funfit_brand_rules collection for rules relevant
to the current brief.

**What to do:**

14. Click the + button after the \"Parse Brief\" node

15. Search for \"Qdrant\" and add a \"Qdrant Vector Store\" node

16. Rename it to \"Get Brand Rules\"

17. Configure it as follows:

  ----------------------- -----------------------------------------------
  **Setting**             **Value**

  **Operation**           Get Many

  **Credential**          CorpFit Qdrant (from Step 3)

  **Collection**          funfit_brand_rules

  **Prompt**              ={{ \$json.module }} {{ \$json.platform }} {{
                          \$json.funnel }} brand voice tone guidelines

  **Limit**               15 (returns top 15 most relevant rules)
  ----------------------- -----------------------------------------------

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **HOW THE SEARCH WORKS**                                              |
|                                                                       |
| The Prompt field is the search query. By including the module (e.g.,  |
| \"meals\"), platform (e.g., \"tiktok\"), and funnel (e.g., \"b2c\"),  |
| Qdrant finds the brand rules most relevant to THIS specific content   |
| piece. The {{ \$json.module }} syntax pulls the value from the        |
| previous Parse Brief node automatically.                              |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **EMBEDDING MODEL REQUIRED**                                          |
|                                                                       |
| Qdrant needs an embedding model to search. In the node settings, look |
| for \"Embedding Model\" and connect it to an Ollama Embeddings node   |
| using nomic-embed-text (already running on your Ollama). Add an       |
| Ollama Embeddings sub-node: Model = nomic-embed-text, Base URL =      |
| http://ollama:11434.                                                  |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

**STEP 5: Add Qdrant Node: Banned Phrases**

This node pulls the banned phrases list so Claude knows what words to
avoid.

**What to do:**

18. Click the + button after the \"Get Brand Rules\" node

19. Add another \"Qdrant Vector Store\" node

20. Rename it to \"Get Banned Phrases\"

21. Configure it:

  ----------------------- -----------------------------------------------
  **Setting**             **Value**

  **Operation**           Get Many

  **Credential**          CorpFit Qdrant

  **Collection**          funfit_banned_phrases

  **Prompt**              banned phrases health claims weight loss
                          medical guarantees pressure shaming

  **Limit**               55 (pull ALL banned phrases --- this is your
                          full safety net)
  ----------------------- -----------------------------------------------

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **WHY PULL ALL BANNED PHRASES?**                                      |
|                                                                       |
| Unlike brand rules (where you only need relevant ones), banned        |
| phrases are a safety net --- you need ALL of them every time. Missing |
| even one could let a policy violation through. With only 55 entries,  |
| the token cost is minimal.                                            |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

**STEP 6: Add Code Node: Assemble Prompt**

This is the brain of the workflow. It takes the static core prompt, adds
the Qdrant results, and creates the final prompt that gets sent to
Claude.

**What to do:**

22. Click the + button after \"Get Banned Phrases\"

23. Search for \"Code\" and add a Code node

24. Rename it to \"Assemble Prompt\"

25. Set Language to \"JavaScript\"

26. Paste the code shown on the next page

**Code for the Assemble Prompt Node:**

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| // ============================================                       |
|                                                                       |
| // ASSEMBLE PROMPT: Static Core + Qdrant Knowledge                    |
|                                                                       |
| // ============================================                       |
|                                                                       |
| // 1. Get the brief values from Parse Brief node                      |
|                                                                       |
| const brief = \$(\'Parse Brief\').first().json;                       |
|                                                                       |
| // 2. Get brand rules from Qdrant (array of results)                  |
|                                                                       |
| const brandRules = \$(\'Get Brand Rules\').all();                     |
|                                                                       |
| const brandRulesText = brandRules                                     |
|                                                                       |
| .map(item =\> {                                                       |
|                                                                       |
| const doc = item.json.document \|\| item.json;                        |
|                                                                       |
| const meta = doc.metadata \|\| {};                                    |
|                                                                       |
| return \`\[\${meta.category \|\| \'general\'}\] \${meta.title \|\|    |
| \'\'}: \${doc.pageContent \|\| meta.content \|\| \'\'}\`;             |
|                                                                       |
| })                                                                    |
|                                                                       |
| .join(\'\\n\');                                                       |
|                                                                       |
| // 3. Get banned phrases from Qdrant                                  |
|                                                                       |
| const bannedPhrases = \$(\'Get Banned Phrases\').all();               |
|                                                                       |
| const bannedText = bannedPhrases                                      |
|                                                                       |
| .map(item =\> {                                                       |
|                                                                       |
| const doc = item.json.document \|\| item.json;                        |
|                                                                       |
| const meta = doc.metadata \|\| {};                                    |
|                                                                       |
| return \`- \"\${meta.phrase \|\| doc.pageContent \|\| \'\'}\"         |
| (\${meta.reason \|\| meta.category \|\| \'\'})\`;                     |
|                                                                       |
| })                                                                    |
|                                                                       |
| .join(\'\\n\');                                                       |
|                                                                       |
| // 4. Static core prompt (agent identity + workflow + format)         |
|                                                                       |
| const staticCore = \`                                                 |
|                                                                       |
| You are ELECTRON-2, the Content Architect for CorpFit.                |
|                                                                       |
| CorpFit is a B2B2C corporate wellness platform.                       |
|                                                                       |
| \## YOUR WORKFLOW                                                     |
|                                                                       |
| 1\. PARSE the production brief                                        |
|                                                                       |
| 2\. PLAN content structure based on platform and module               |
|                                                                       |
| 3\. CREATE hooks, script, captions, CTA                               |
|                                                                       |
| 4\. CHECK against banned phrases and safety rules                     |
|                                                                       |
| 5\. OUTPUT in the required format with emoji headers                  |
|                                                                       |
| \## OUTPUT FORMAT (MANDATORY)                                         |
|                                                                       |
| \-\--START CONTENT PACKAGE\-\--                                       |
|                                                                       |
| BRIEF SUMMARY: \[recap the brief in 2 lines\]                         |
|                                                                       |
| HOOKS: \[2-3 hook options\]                                           |
|                                                                       |
| SCRIPT: \[time-coded script\]                                         |
|                                                                       |
| ON-SCREEN TEXT: \[key phrases with timing\]                           |
|                                                                       |
| STORYBOARD: \[scene-by-scene description\]                            |
|                                                                       |
| CAPTION (SHORT): \[under 150 chars\]                                  |
|                                                                       |
| CAPTION (LONG): \[extended with hashtags\]                            |
|                                                                       |
| CTA: \[call-to-action\]                                               |
|                                                                       |
| DISCLAIMER: \[if needed, or \'none\'\]                                |
|                                                                       |
| SELF-CHECK REPORT: \[confirm no banned phrases, brand compliance\]    |
|                                                                       |
| \-\--END CONTENT PACKAGE\-\--                                         |
|                                                                       |
| \## SAFE FRAMING RULES                                                |
|                                                                       |
| \- Use \'may support\' instead of \'cures/treats\'                    |
|                                                                       |
| \- Use \'consider trying\' instead of \'you must/should\'             |
|                                                                       |
| \- Use \'research suggests\' instead of \'proven/guaranteed\'         |
|                                                                       |
| \- Use \'support your journey\' instead of \'lose weight\'            |
|                                                                       |
| \- Add disclaimers for any health-adjacent content                    |
|                                                                       |
| \`;                                                                   |
|                                                                       |
| // 5. Assemble the complete system prompt                             |
|                                                                       |
| const systemPrompt = \`\${staticCore}                                 |
|                                                                       |
| \## BRAND RULES (from CorpFit Knowledge Base)                         |
|                                                                       |
| \${brandRulesText}                                                    |
|                                                                       |
| \## BANNED PHRASES (NEVER use these in any content)                   |
|                                                                       |
| \${bannedText}                                                        |
|                                                                       |
| \`;                                                                   |
|                                                                       |
| // 6. Create the production brief (user message)                      |
|                                                                       |
| const userMessage = \`PRODUCTION BRIEF:                               |
|                                                                       |
| \- Topic: \${brief.topic}                                             |
|                                                                       |
| \- Platform: \${brief.platform}                                       |
|                                                                       |
| \- Module: \${brief.module}                                           |
|                                                                       |
| \- Funnel: \${brief.funnel}                                           |
|                                                                       |
| \- Duration: \${brief.duration}                                       |
|                                                                       |
| Generate a complete content package following the output format       |
| above.\`;                                                             |
|                                                                       |
| // 7. Return both prompts for the HTTP Request node                   |
|                                                                       |
| return \[{                                                            |
|                                                                       |
| json: {                                                               |
|                                                                       |
| systemPrompt,                                                         |
|                                                                       |
| userMessage,                                                          |
|                                                                       |
| brief                                                                 |
|                                                                       |
| }                                                                     |
|                                                                       |
| }\];                                                                  |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

**STEP 7: Update the HTTP Request Node (Claude API)**

Now update your existing Claude API node to use the assembled prompt
from the Code node instead of the hardcoded prompt.

**What to do:**

27. Click on your existing HTTP Request node

28. In the Body section, update the JSON to reference the assembled
    prompt:

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| {                                                                     |
|                                                                       |
| \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-20250514\",                              |
|                                                                       |
| \"max_tokens\": 4096,                                                 |
|                                                                       |
| \"system\": \"{{ \$json.systemPrompt }}\",                            |
|                                                                       |
| \"messages\": \[                                                      |
|                                                                       |
| {                                                                     |
|                                                                       |
| \"role\": \"user\",                                                   |
|                                                                       |
| \"content\": \"{{ \$json.userMessage }}\"                             |
|                                                                       |
| }                                                                     |
|                                                                       |
| \]                                                                    |
|                                                                       |
| }                                                                     |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **IMPORTANT: Escape Characters**                                      |
|                                                                       |
| n8n expressions inside JSON can be tricky. If you get errors, try     |
| using the Expression Editor (click the gear icon next to the Body     |
| field) and build the JSON there. Make sure the systemPrompt and       |
| userMessage don\'t contain unescaped quotes that break the JSON.      |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **ALTERNATIVE APPROACH**                                              |
|                                                                       |
| If JSON escaping gives you trouble, you can use a second Code node    |
| before the HTTP Request that builds the entire API request body       |
| programmatically. This avoids escaping issues entirely. Ask Claude to |
| help you write this if needed.                                        |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

